values: I learned a very valuable lesson today. Never mess with the setting on your computer.

I work in the fast paced world of fast food. So i was doing my thing in drive thru tonight and the strangest thing happened. This man asked how much the order behind him cost. Slightly bemused I told him the amount. Giving a nod the gentleman handed me back his credit card saying that he'll pay for the other car's order. After swiping the card I asked why the man had done so. He simply turned to me and said he was grateful that the man behind him turned off lights, nothing more. cerin

I should really stop listening to Doubt. Unfortunaly Confidence has gone on vacation with muse so now I am left all alone with Doubt and Lathargy. Man I hate this time of year. Curse you 50% off coupons!

Today my artist Kittara and my ex-artist Kyo went to drawing class. Sensei continued to fix their styles and the like but he told me something I needed to know. He told me to find my own style. Something I've always wondered how to actually do.    At first the news almost sent me into a fit, but then he explained himself. 

"What do you like about your favorite books and manga? The character depth, the back story? Well take those things you like and try to emulate them. Eventually you will have your own style to work with."

With that nugget of advice I shall push forth and write. Thank you Sensei!!!!

Story: HP and the Alchemists
Number of pages completed: 1 ^.^;
In the Beta stage: No
Reason for this atrocity: School and closing shifts at work
Have you written anything?!?!: Yes i have drafted some in my notebook and will continue to do so until I'm                                                        satisfied with the story flow.

I've devised this method of keeping my fans up to date on the latest in hopes that I still have your support.

Bring the steaming mug to my lips I tug the fleece blanket closer. With a heavy sigh and an equally heavy heart I sit coldly in front of my glowing screen. Secretly wishing that the cold feeling deep within would be easily remedied. It seems as though my Muse has flown south for the winter.

As of right now I am striving to be one of those writers who update at least once a month. So far that isn't happening. I don't want to work on fanfiction right now. 

I want my original story back. It was only a third done. TT.TT Curse you Sezka! and no Flint I have yahoo. No MSN for Siv.

DeviantArt: Like OMFG, you like "Ripped" this person off and stuff. And even though you, like didn't even say you owned that mass of pixels and junk we're so totally going to take it down.

Copyright protection is getting way out of hand. I just claimed that that paticular item was my favorite character and they go flying off the handle! Ok I am going to break down how fandom works here:

you create concept>>people like concept>>people tell other people they like concept>>word is spread>>creator of concept is now more popular than ever.  All is happy, all is well.  The End!

Certain copyright bullshit is added and the whole thing goes>>>>>poof

Well then,  copyright this!!!!!!!!!!!

Have I ever mentioned how the sound of pencil on paper is a comforting sound? Or the gentle tac tak tac of the keyboard beneath my finger tips makes me feel like a goddess? 

My greatest aspiration is to one day have my work be well know to a certain extent. Oh well back to practice.

I've always felt out of place in the artist community. But today i found out that I really like photoshop. coloring coloring add another do di do! Ah hem!  Well anyway  if flint will sent me the info about long posts I'll be actually uploading more junk of mine! Yay me.

Siv Fish by ~kittara-jaganshi on deviantART

This is what i want to look like.

Alright time to rant for the day.  Sitting on the bus today I got into a random conversation with a kid in my Japanese class. Turns out he's a published writer with two books out already. TT.TT I feel so slackerish.

All I've ever written that was original will forever remain in the depths of my bookself.
